Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff; white slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 131 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Nikasagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0175.33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1099)
